msgid "Security model, trust boundaries, and production hardening guidance for Klein for Ray."
msgstr "Klein for Ray 的安全模型、信任边界和生产加固指南。"

msgid "Security"
msgstr "安全"

msgid ""
"Klein is a distributed execution library for trusted Python applications. It is not a sandbox, an"
" authorization layer, or a tenant-isolation system. A user who can submit a Klein job can execute"
" Python on Ray workers, open network connections, access worker-visible files and environment "
"variables, and use the credentials available to that workload."
msgstr ""
"Klein 是面向受信任 Python 应用的分布式执行库。它不是沙箱、授权层或租户隔离系统。能够提交 Klein 作业的用户可以在 Ray worker 上执行 "
"Python、打开网络连接、访问 worker 可见的文件和环境变量，并使用该工作负载可用的凭据。"

msgid ""
"This page explains deployment security. To report a suspected vulnerability, use the private "
"process in the repository's [security policy](https://github.com/yuchen-"
"ecnu/klein/blob/main/SECURITY.md), not a public issue."
msgstr ""
"本页说明部署安全。若要报告疑似漏洞，请使用仓库[安全策略](https://github.com/yuchen-"
"ecnu/klein/blob/main/SECURITY.md)中的私密流程，不要提交公开 issue。"

msgid "Trust model"
msgstr "信任模型"

msgid "Treat the following principals and artifacts as trusted:"
msgstr "将以下主体和构件视为受信任："

msgid "everyone allowed to submit code or connect a Python client to the Ray cluster;"
msgstr "所有获准提交代码或将 Python 客户端连接到 Ray 集群的人员；"

msgid ""
"application code, UDFs, serializers, source and sink implementations, and their Python/native "
"dependencies;"
msgstr "应用代码、UDF、序列化器、数据源和 Sink 实现及其 Python/原生依赖；"

msgid "every process that can write to a checkpoint prefix;"
msgstr "所有能够写入检查点前缀的进程；"

msgid "the Ray cluster, its node images, runtime environments, and administrators;"
msgstr "Ray 集群、其节点镜像、运行时环境和管理员；"

msgid "the platform identities that can read secrets or connector data."
msgstr "能够读取密钥或连接器数据的平台身份。"

msgid ""
"Treat source records, connector services, users of an application built on Klein, and network "
"clients outside the protected cluster boundary as untrusted unless the application establishes a "
"narrower contract."
msgstr "除非应用建立了更严格的契约，否则应将数据源记录、连接器服务、基于 Klein 构建的应用用户以及受保护集群边界外的网络客户端视为不受信任。"

msgid ""
"Do not restore a checkpoint from an untrusted or shared-writable location. Klein checkpoint "
"metadata, source state, managed state, and prepared sink committables can contain Python pickle "
"payloads. Deserializing a malicious pickle can execute code with the worker's identity. A stored "
"checksum detects accidental corruption relative to checkpoint metadata; it is not a signature and"
" does not make an attacker-controlled checkpoint authentic."
msgstr ""
"不要从不受信任或可由多个主体写入的位置恢复检查点。Klein 检查点元数据、数据源状态、托管状态和已预备的 Sink 可提交项可能包含 Python pickle 载荷。反序列化恶意 "
"pickle 会以 worker 身份执行代码。存储的校验和只能根据检查点元数据检测意外损坏；它不是签名，也不能证明由攻击者控制的检查点可信。"

msgid "Responsibility boundaries"
msgstr "责任边界"

msgid ""
"Security is the composition of Klein, Ray, the deployment platform, and the application. No one "
"layer compensates automatically for a missing control in another."
msgstr "安全由 Klein、Ray、部署平台和应用共同构成。任何一层都不会自动弥补另一层缺失的控制措施。"

msgid "Owner"
msgstr "责任方"

msgid "Responsible for"
msgstr "负责内容"

msgid "Not provided by that layer"
msgstr "该层不提供"

msgid "Klein"
msgstr "Klein"

msgid ""
"Default loopback Dashboard binding; refusal of a non-loopback binding unless explicitly "
"overridden; Host-header and same-origin checks; bounded Dashboard request bodies; key-name-based "
"redaction in published configuration and structured log fields; checkpoint size/checksum "
"validation before managed-state payload use; documenting source/sink recovery boundaries."
msgstr ""
"默认绑定回环地址的 Dashboard；除非显式覆盖，否则拒绝绑定非回环地址；Host 请求头和同源检查；限制 Dashboard "
"请求正文大小；根据键名对已发布配置和结构化日志字段进行脱敏；使用托管状态载荷前验证检查点大小/校验和；记录数据源/Sink 恢复边界。"

msgid ""
"Authentication, authorization, TLS, hostile-code sandboxing, secret storage, tenant isolation, "
"checkpoint signatures, record-level encryption, or an audit log independent of Ray."
msgstr "身份验证、授权、TLS、恶意代码沙箱、密钥存储、租户隔离、检查点签名、记录级加密，或独立于 Ray 的审计日志。"

msgid "Ray"
msgstr "Ray"

msgid ""
"Running actors/tasks, namespaces, runtime environments, Object Store, worker/actor logs, metrics,"
" cluster connectivity, and the authentication/TLS features configured by the Ray operator."
msgstr "运行 actor/任务、命名空间、运行时环境、Object Store、worker/actor 日志、指标、集群连接，以及 Ray 运维方配置的身份验证/TLS 功能。"

msgid ""
"Klein-specific authorization or isolation between mutually untrusted Klein jobs. A Ray namespace "
"avoids actor-name collisions; it is not an access-control boundary."
msgstr "Klein 专用授权，或互不信任的 Klein 作业之间的隔离。Ray 命名空间可避免 actor 名称冲突，但不是访问控制边界。"

msgid "Platform operator"
msgstr "平台运维方"

msgid ""
"Network isolation, firewall and ingress policy, TLS termination, Ray authentication, "
"Kubernetes/cloud IAM, node and container hardening, image provenance, secret delivery, object-"
"store IAM/encryption/versioning, log/metric access, backups, and separation of security domains."
msgstr ""
"网络隔离、防火墙和入口策略、TLS 终止、Ray 身份验证、Kubernetes/云 IAM、节点和容器加固、镜像来源、密钥交付、对象存储 "
"IAM/加密/版本控制、日志/指标访问、备份以及安全域隔离。"

msgid "Correct UDF behavior, safe application logging, connector semantics, or sink idempotency."
msgstr "正确的 UDF 行为、安全的应用日志记录、连接器语义或 Sink 幂等性。"

msgid "Application owner"
msgstr "应用负责人"

msgid ""
"Trusted dependencies and code review; input validation; UDF/resource limits; connector credential"
" use; state/schema choices; sensitive-data classification; safe job/operator names; output "
"authorization, idempotency, and retention."
msgstr "受信任依赖和代码审查；输入验证；UDF/资源限制；连接器凭据使用；状态/模式选择；敏感数据分类；安全的作业/算子名称；输出授权、幂等性和保留。"

msgid "Cluster isolation or platform controls that were never configured."
msgstr "从未配置的集群隔离或平台控制。"

msgid ""
"Ray's own security guidance requires a controlled network and trusted code and recommends "
"separate clusters for workloads that need isolation. Configure current Ray controls according to "
"the [Ray security documentation](https://docs.ray.io/en/latest/ray-security/index.html)."
msgstr ""
"Ray 自身的安全指南要求使用受控网络和受信任代码，并建议需要隔离的工作负载使用独立集群。请按照 [Ray 安全文档](https://docs.ray.io/en/latest/ray-"
"security/index.html)配置当前 Ray 控制措施。"

msgid "Python code, UDFs, and pickle"
msgstr "Python 代码、UDF 和 pickle"

msgid ""
"Klein sends application functions and operator objects to Ray workers and uses Python "
"serialization for application-defined state. This has several consequences:"
msgstr "Klein 会将应用函数和算子对象发送到 Ray worker，并使用 Python 序列化存储应用定义的状态。这会带来以下影响："

msgid ""
"UDFs, custom sources, custom sinks, serializers, callbacks, and dependencies have the same "
"effective trust as the job submitter."
msgstr "UDF、自定义数据源、自定义 Sink、序列化器、回调和依赖项与作业提交者具有相同的实际信任级别。"

msgid "Pickle and cloudpickle are data/code transport formats, not safe parsers for hostile bytes."
msgstr "pickle 和 cloudpickle 是数据/代码传输格式，不是用于处理恶意字节的安全解析器。"

msgid ""
"Moving or renaming Python classes and modules can make a trusted checkpoint unreadable even when "
"no attacker is involved."
msgstr "即使不存在攻击者，移动或重命名 Python 类和模块也可能导致受信任的检查点无法读取。"

msgid ""
"Deserialization must happen only in an environment whose code and dependency versions are "
"controlled by the operator."
msgstr "只能在代码和依赖版本受运维方控制的环境中执行反序列化。"

msgid ""
"Use signed or otherwise provenance-checked application artifacts, pin dependencies, scan the "
"final worker image, and review custom serialization hooks. Parse untrusted external data with a "
"constrained data format such as JSON, Avro, or Parquet before it becomes application state. Do "
"not call `pickle.loads()` on a record supplied by an external user."
msgstr ""
"使用已签名或通过其他方式验证来源的应用构件，固定依赖，扫描最终 worker 镜像，并审查自定义序列化钩子。在不受信任的外部数据成为应用状态之前，使用 JSON、Avro 或 Parquet "
"等受约束的数据格式解析它。不要对外部用户提供的记录调用 `pickle.loads()`。"

msgid "For checkpoint storage:"
msgstr "对于检查点存储："

msgid "Give the job identity read/write access only to its dedicated prefix."
msgstr "仅授予作业身份对其专用前缀的读写权限。"

msgid "Give restore tooling read access only to explicitly approved prefixes."
msgstr "仅授予恢复工具对明确批准前缀的读取权限。"

msgid ""
"Enable transport encryption, server-side encryption, versioning, retention, and access logging at"
" the object store."
msgstr "在对象存储上启用传输加密、服务端加密、版本控制、保留和访问日志。"

msgid "Separate prefixes and credentials across production, staging, and tenants."
msgstr "在生产、预发布和不同租户之间隔离前缀和凭据。"

msgid ""
"Treat deletion, replacement of `_metadata`, or writes to `shared/` and `taskowned/` as security-"
"sensitive actions."
msgstr "将删除、替换 `_metadata`，或写入 `shared/` 和 `taskowned/` 视为安全敏感操作。"

msgid ""
"Never copy only `chk-N/_metadata` and assume the checkpoint is self-contained; it can reference "
"state objects elsewhere in the job prefix."
msgstr "绝不能只复制 `chk-N/_metadata` 就假定检查点是自包含的；它可能引用作业前缀中其他位置的状态对象。"

msgid ""
"See [Checkpoint storage](checkpoint-storage.md) for the actual publication and validation "
"behavior."
msgstr "实际发布和验证行为请参阅[检查点存储](checkpoint-storage.md)。"

msgid "Dashboard and control APIs"
msgstr "Dashboard 和控制 API"

msgid ""
"`ray-klein dashboard` serves a separate Klein HTTP page. It is not part of the Ray Dashboard and "
"has no built-in user authentication or TLS."
msgstr "`ray-klein dashboard` 提供独立的 Klein HTTP 页面。它不是 Ray Dashboard 的一部分，也没有内置用户身份验证或 TLS。"

msgid ""
"The default listener is `127.0.0.1:8266`. Keep that default and use an SSH tunnel or port-forward"
" when possible:"
msgstr "默认监听地址为 `127.0.0.1:8266`。请保留该默认值，并尽可能使用 SSH 隧道或端口转发："

msgid ""
"The server refuses a non-loopback listener unless `--allow-unauthenticated` is present. That flag"
" only acknowledges the risk; it does not add protection. A remote listener exposes job topology "
"and status and can submit supported operator-rescale actions."
msgstr ""
"除非提供 `--allow-"
"unauthenticated`，否则服务器会拒绝监听非回环地址。该标志只表示已知晓风险，不会增加任何保护。远程监听器会暴露作业拓扑和状态，并可提交受支持的算子扩缩操作。"

msgid "If remote access is required:"
msgstr "如果必须远程访问："

msgid "place the listener behind an authenticated, authorized TLS reverse proxy;"
msgstr "将监听器置于具有身份验证和授权的 TLS 反向代理之后；"

msgid "restrict ingress to the operations network and approved identities;"
msgstr "将入口限制在运维网络和获批身份；"

msgid "preserve or rewrite `Host` to a host trusted by the listener;"
msgstr "保留 `Host`，或将其重写为监听器信任的主机；"

msgid "enforce request, rate, and session limits at the proxy;"
msgstr "在代理处实施请求、速率和会话限制；"

msgid ""
"monitor control requests at the proxy, because Klein suppresses the base HTTP access log to avoid"
" leaking job identifiers;"
msgstr "在代理处监控控制请求，因为 Klein 为避免泄漏作业标识符而禁用了基础 HTTP 访问日志；"

msgid ""
"do not rely on the built-in Host-header, same-origin, CSP, or frame checks as substitutes for "
"authentication."
msgstr "不要依赖内置 Host 请求头、同源、CSP 或框架检查来替代身份验证。"

msgid ""
"The Python state API and CLI connect through Ray to a detached state actor and JobManager. Any "
"principal with sufficient Ray access to use those actors must already be trusted to observe and "
"control the jobs. Protect Ray Client, Ray Jobs, the Ray Dashboard, GCS, and worker ports "
"according to the platform's Ray deployment. Ray token authentication is defense in depth, not a "
"replacement for network isolation; see [Ray token authentication](https://docs.ray.io/en/latest"
"/ray-security/token-auth.html)."
msgstr ""
"Python 状态 API 和 CLI 通过 Ray 连接到分离的状态 actor 和 JobManager。任何拥有足够 Ray 访问权限、可以使用这些 actor "
"的主体，都必须已被信任可以观察和控制作业。请根据平台的 Ray 部署保护 Ray Client、Ray Jobs、Ray Dashboard、GCS 和 worker 端口。Ray token "
"身份验证属于纵深防御，不能替代网络隔离；请参阅 [Ray token 身份验证](https://docs.ray.io/en/latest/ray-security/token-"
"auth.html)。"

msgid ""
"Setting `observability.dashboard.enabled=false` stops publication to Klein's state actor. It does"
" not disable Ray logs, Ray metrics, checkpointing, or every way trusted Ray code can address job "
"actors."
msgstr ""
"设置 `observability.dashboard.enabled=false` 会停止向 Klein 状态 actor 发布信息。它不会禁用 Ray 日志、Ray "
"指标、检查点，也不会阻止受信任 Ray 代码通过所有其他方式寻址作业 actor。"

msgid "Credentials and sensitive data"
msgstr "凭据和敏感数据"

msgid ""
"Prefer workload identity, instance roles, mounted secret files, or a platform secret provider. "
"Avoid literals in source code, Table DDL, command lines, resource plans, and committed "
"configuration. Restrict each job identity to the specific source, sink, and checkpoint resources "
"it needs."
msgstr ""
"优先使用工作负载身份、实例角色、挂载的密钥文件或平台密钥提供方。避免在源代码、Table DDL、命令行、资源计划和已提交配置中使用字面量。将每个作业身份限制为仅能访问所需的特定数据源、Sink"
" 和检查点资源。"

msgid "Klein applies limited, key-name-based redaction:"
msgstr "Klein 仅提供有限的、基于键名的脱敏："

msgid ""
"published configuration recursively redacts keys resembling passwords, secrets, tokens, "
"credentials, access keys, private keys, and API keys;"
msgstr "已发布配置会递归脱敏名称类似密码、密钥、token、凭据、访问密钥、私钥和 API 密钥的键；"

msgid "structured Klein log fields redact a similar set of names;"
msgstr "Klein 结构化日志字段会脱敏一组类似的名称；"

msgid "Redis omits its password from the configuration object's representation."
msgstr "Redis 会在配置对象的表示形式中省略密码。"

msgid ""
"Redaction is a guardrail, not a data-loss-prevention system. It does not scan free-form strings "
"or record values, and application or third-party loggers can bypass it. Do not put sensitive "
"values in:"
msgstr "脱敏是一项防护措施，并非数据防泄漏系统。它不会扫描自由格式字符串或记录值，应用或第三方日志记录器也可能绕过它。不要将敏感值放入："

msgid "job, operator, task, metric, or namespace names;"
msgstr "作业、算子、任务、指标或命名空间名称；"

msgid "record values sent to a console sink;"
msgstr "发送到控制台 Sink 的记录值；"

msgid "exception messages or manually formatted log text;"
msgstr "异常消息或手动格式化的日志文本；"

msgid "metric labels;"
msgstr "指标标签；"

msgid "connector URLs or checkpoint paths;"
msgstr "连接器 URL 或检查点路径；"

msgid "arbitrary configuration keys whose name does not look secret."
msgstr "名称看起来不像密钥的任意配置键。"

msgid ""
"Configuration and connector objects are serialized to workers. Iceberg catalog properties, "
"checkpoint storage options, Kafka/Redis/RocketMQ settings, and custom source/sink objects "
"therefore remain visible to trusted worker code and may also appear in process memory. Rotate a "
"credential after suspected exposure and review Ray logs, runtime-environment metadata, shell "
"history, and object-store access logs."
msgstr ""
"配置和连接器对象会被序列化到 worker。因此，Iceberg catalog 属性、检查点存储选项、Kafka/Redis/RocketMQ 设置以及自定义数据源/Sink 对象仍对受信任的"
" worker 代码可见，也可能出现在进程内存中。怀疑凭据暴露后应立即轮换，并审查 Ray 日志、运行时环境元数据、shell 历史和对象存储访问日志。"

msgid "Multi-tenancy"
msgstr "多租户"

msgid ""
"Klein does not provide isolation between hostile jobs in one Ray cluster. Per-job Ray namespaces "
"prevent named-actor collisions and help operations find a job, but they do not prevent another "
"trusted cluster client or workload from discovering actors, consuming cluster resources, "
"accessing worker-visible credentials, or attacking shared services."
msgstr ""
"Klein 不提供同一 Ray 集群内恶意作业之间的隔离。每个作业的 Ray 命名空间可防止具名 actor 冲突，并帮助运维人员查找作业，但无法阻止另一个受信任的集群客户端或工作负载发现 "
"actor、消耗集群资源、访问 worker 可见的凭据或攻击共享服务。"

msgid ""
"Use separate Ray clusters, service accounts, networks, checkpoint roots, connector identities, "
"log stores, and encryption domains when workloads or teams do not fully trust one another. "
"Resource quotas and placement groups are capacity controls, not security boundaries. In-process "
"debug mode provides even less isolation and must not be used to evaluate production security."
msgstr ""
"当工作负载或团队之间并非完全互信时，请使用独立的 Ray "
"集群、服务账户、网络、检查点根目录、连接器身份、日志存储和加密域。资源配额和放置组是容量控制，而不是安全边界。进程内调试模式的隔离性更弱，不得用于评估生产安全。"

msgid "Production hardening checklist"
msgstr "生产加固检查清单"

msgid "Allow only reviewed identities to submit Ray jobs or connect Ray clients."
msgstr "仅允许经过审查的身份提交 Ray 作业或连接 Ray 客户端。"

msgid "Keep all Ray and Klein control endpoints off the public internet."
msgstr "不要将任何 Ray 和 Klein 控制端点暴露到公共互联网。"

msgid ""
"Enable the Ray authentication and encryption controls supported by the deployed Ray version, plus"
" network isolation and external authorization."
msgstr "启用已部署 Ray 版本支持的身份验证和加密控制，并配合网络隔离和外部授权。"

msgid "Run mutually untrusted workloads in separate Ray clusters."
msgstr "在独立的 Ray 集群中运行互不信任的工作负载。"

msgid "Use immutable, scanned head and worker images with the same pinned dependencies."
msgstr "对 head 和 worker 使用依赖固定且经过扫描的相同不可变镜像。"

msgid ""
"Run workers without unnecessary host mounts, cloud permissions, Linux capabilities, or access to "
"another job's secrets."
msgstr "运行 worker 时，不要提供不必要的主机挂载、云权限、Linux capability 或对其他作业密钥的访问权限。"

msgid ""
"Keep the Klein Dashboard on loopback, or place it behind authenticated TLS ingress with audit "
"logging."
msgstr "将 Klein Dashboard 保持在回环地址上，或置于带审计日志、经过身份验证的 TLS 入口之后。"

msgid ""
"Give each job a dedicated, versioned, encrypted checkpoint prefix and test restore with the same "
"least-privilege identity."
msgstr "为每个作业提供专用、版本化、加密的检查点前缀，并使用相同的最小权限身份测试恢复。"

msgid ""
"Use different identities for sources, sinks, and administrative recovery when the platform can "
"support that separation."
msgstr "当平台支持这种隔离时，为数据源、Sink 和管理恢复使用不同身份。"

msgid ""
"Export Ray/Klein logs and metrics to access-controlled durable stores; test that secret values do"
" not appear in a representative failure."
msgstr "将 Ray/Klein 日志和指标导出到受访问控制的持久存储；测试具有代表性的故障中不会出现密钥值。"

msgid ""
"Define credential rotation, artifact rollback, checkpoint revocation, and incident-response "
"procedures before launch."
msgstr "上线前定义凭据轮换、构件回滚、检查点撤销和事件响应流程。"

msgid ""
"For operational release gates, use the [Production readiness checklist](production-readiness.md)."
" For upgrade and rollback security, including trusted checkpoint handling, see [Upgrade Klein "
"jobs](upgrading.md)."
msgstr "运维发布门槛请使用[生产就绪检查清单](production-readiness.md)。升级和回滚安全（包括受信任检查点处理）请参阅[升级 Klein 作业](upgrading.md)。"
